==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sally Lunn
<hw>Sal"ly Lunn"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[From a woman, <ets>Sally
Lunn</ets>, who is said to have first made the cakes, and sold them in
the streets of Bath, Eng.]</ety> <def>A tea cake slightly sweetened, and
raised with yeast, baked in the form of biscuits or in a thin loaf, and
eaten hot with butter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sallyman</ent>⟦br⟧
